{"type":"message","id":"df86a858","parentId":"3f251812","timestamp":"2026-03-07T02:15:01.573Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The qmd index.yml looks correct - it has `memory-dir-main`. But OpenClaw is still querying `memory-dir-main-2`. This means the gateway is caching the resolved collection names from when the state was different. The gateway needs a proper restart.\n\nLet me check if the gateway actually restarted by looking at the PID and logs.\n\nThe RPC probe failed with \"pairing required\" - this means the CLI can't talk to the gateway directly, but the agent session (which is running through the gateway) should have access.\n\nWait - the `openclaw gateway restart` command failed with \"missing tool result in session history; inserted synthetic error result for transcript repair.\" - this is a synthetic error from OpenClaw itself when there's a missing tool result in the transcript. \n\nThat error doesn't necessarily mean the restart failed. The \"pairing required\" message might just mean the CLI token needs to re-pair after the restart, but my agent session is still connected through the gateway. The real issue is that the gateway process with PID 4443 is still running from before my fix, so it's still holding the old `memory-dir-main-2` collection name in memory. I need to actually kill and restart the gateway process directly rather than relying on the restart command.","thinkingSignature":""},{"type":"toolCall","id":"toolu_01166mU8XLVyLqaHtr3rQJaW","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"tail -20 /tmp/openclaw/openclaw-2026-03-06.log 2>/dev/null"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"anthropic","model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","usage":{"input":1,"output":420,"cacheRead":38234,"cacheWrite":219,"totalTokens":38874,"cost":{"input":0.000003,"output":0.0063,"cacheRead":0.0114702,"cacheWrite":0.00082125,"total":0.01859445}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1772849691624}}
